The paper deals with the problem of sub-Nyquist sampling and reconstruction of signals, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The focus is on sparse signals, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and compressive sensing (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed methods through simulations, which is a topic in statistical learning (cs.SI).
